Accessibility
Accessibility
MIT is committed to providing an environment that is accessible to individuals with disabilities. If you cannot access content or use features on our website due to a disability, please
let us know
.
MIT resources available to individuals with disabilities:
MIT Campus Accessibility Map
Includes locations of elevators, accessible parking, ramps, restrooms, and more.
Disability and Access Services
Ensures equal access for students with disabilities.
Accessibility & Usability
Provides guidance to the MIT community with accessibility and usability of content and features of MIT websites, applications, and courseware.
Captioning
Provides resources on captioning and accessibility of digital content
.
Assistive Technology
Provides guidance and services about assistive technologies for persons with disabilities at MIT.
Human Resources Disability Services
Provides effective and reasonable accommodations to employees with documented disabilities.
